annotation.TEXT: There's a 1-up, but what if I keep going?
Okay, so the key is right here...
Be careful not to run into the sides of the munchers. Yoshi's tough shoes won't protect you there!
Alright, I'm done with this level, and I guess it's bonus game time again.
Gulp!
Hmm... Looks like I can go left or right. Well, what's to the right?
It doesn't look like there's anything else up there...
Looks like the Dino-Rhino family resides here too.
Okay, so that unlocks 4-4. However, I'm going to head back to the desert and play 5-2 now.
(Wow, no votes for 3-1 this time? That's somewhat surprising.)
Now to get the last two, which shouldn't be a problem.
But, at present, it looks like I'll be starting with this fortress next time! To be continued...
SMB3-style in-and-out munchers. (Good thing for the red switch! I don't know how I would've ever made that jump if it was slightly longer!)
Barf!
Gulp!
Be careful of their stunning quakes!
But, yeah, as nathanisbored had informed me, there's hidden stuff above where those two Boomerang Bros. were here.
...and apparently more Lakitus offscreen. Well, I think I know what the silver P-switch is for!
Found it! And it only took tearing apart two-thirds of a pyramid to find it!
Nuts. I caught the wall there, but no dive bomb occurred...
Wow, my aim was terrible there!
Thank you, green switch!
Alright, let's go back for the shell, and kill anything that I can along the way.
Hey, does the screen scroll up? Nope, I guess not.
Well, ZSNES decided to desynch my footage shortly after I started looking. However, nothing of major importance was lost, as I never found the darned exit!
And hopefully, that's that... Hey, wait a minute! Looking back, I could've just cape flown normally over that whole part and it would've probably been easier!
I doubt it...
...you can enter it!
Clouds, underground? That's way too unrealistic!
There's a cape, and the letter "A" written in purple coins... I'm going to be spin jump flying, aren't I?
Okay, now that I made that jump without screwing up, there's a little something hidden around here...
Yep, looks like we're going up! (I wonder if I'll need the shell...)

Huh? The hidden 1-up isn't here this time! But, it was there last time I played the bonus game, earlier in this video, and both levels were on the main overworld map... I'm guessing one of them is in a level number above 100, and the other one is below 100.
Man, that sucks...
I don't think there was a secret exit in that ghost house, but if I'm wrong, let me know!
That's not how you quake! THIS is how you quake!
Oh, so it's actually a P-switch! Of course, to get rid of the cyan ! blocks in my way. (A vine would've just hit the low ceiling anyway.)
Yoshi takes priority over my reserve item! I can get more flowers later.
SCORE!!! And with that, I get to enter the bonus game again!
...and (facepalm), the keyhole is right over here.
6-life combo! And another silver P-switch appears! Wow, you can really rack up a large number of lives in this room!
Remember how I said this sideways pipe seemed suspicious? Well, hit the P-switch here, and...
Namely, this P-switch, which I guess was sitting on an offscreen turn block.
Just as soon as I stop getting beaten up, I'll show it off.
Awesome, but it's just coins and a feather. Also, I'd better hurry up!
I wonder what silly name this world has... ("Flying Pig Hills", or something like that, perhaps? I'm sure PeejsterM will let me know!)
That pipe looks interesting, but it's not really. Also, looks like the green ! blocks really help here!
You saw nothing. (Except for me Start+Selecting out of the level when I screwed up and fell there!)
MOOOOOONNN!!! But, what if I keep going... Oh, I can't go any further. Okay, I'll take the moon!
And yeah, this is how you're supposed to reach the secret exit. However, there's one other thing that can be done with the P-switch...
Brick pyramids? Now I know this was inspired by that SMB3 level (2-3)!
Still no sign of the secret exit, though, and none of these areas scroll vertically...
I'm sure there's a P-switch in one of these! (Watch it be in the very last brick...)
Aha! I do need the shell to hit this block, which probably contains a vine or something. (Also, no reset door? Does that mean I would've had to suicide if I wasted the shell?)
So, did those coins up there mean something? I must know!
I'd tried using the P-switch everywhere in the level, and I didn't see anything unusual appear. So, yeah. If anyone knows where it is, let me know!
Found the P-switch again...
Okay, so we've got a silver P-switch and a pipe Lakitu...
Well, I found a 1-up right away...
Uh, oh! I see cutoff! This hack's not gonna be accepted at SMW Central!
Also, I apparently really suck at the bonus game this time...
Midpoint already. This seems easier than the last few levels I've done. (Gee, I wonder why that is?)
Yep, and now I bet that arrow to the right at the start has meaning now.
Oh, crap! Uh, bye, Yoshi!
No fire snakes, but Fire Bros. are certainly showing up (and falling offscreen in that silly way again).
That opens 4-2, but I've gotta go back to 4-1 and find that keyhole. (And not spit the key into a pit!)
Nothing! (At least, I don't see anything there...)
I suspect that the last Yoshi coin is hidden offscreen somewhere, like in a previous level...
Normally, I wouldn't fly over large chunks of the level like this, but I'm pressed for time. Doesn't look like I've skipped too much though.
Well, that's all the Yoshi coins, but I didn't see any keyhole...
Yep, there's the key. Now I just need to find the keyhole...
That unlocks a fortress, but I'm not heading there yet. Instead, I'm going to fly all the way over to 4-1, since that was the next most popular vote.
It's time for another episode of Super SIG World 21! Now, before we get to the voting results, I'm going to revisit 5-1 and show a few things I previously missed...
But, where could that last Yoshi coin be? It isn't offscreen in this room, is it?
More SMB3 inspiration, I take it? This one seems to be loosely based off of 2-3, except without the fire snakes.
Gah! Wasn't paying attention...
I'm going to scout out the area ahead just to make sure (and clear out some enemies along the way).
There seems to be a ceiling here, but it doesn't stretch all the way to the left. However, I don't think there's anything important offscreen here...
I didn't know disco was popular in the desert...
Man, if only I had the blue switch active... Wait, I don't need the blue switch to hit those!
D'oh! I didn't mean to do that! Well, I'll just keep an eye out for the keyhole anyway, then get the secret exit on my next visit.
Ooh, we've got Sledge Bros. here!
Wow, midpoint already? And an ON/OFF block, which I'm sure must be changed to OFF.
Well, what do you know? The silver munchers insta-kill you, even if you're riding Yoshi!
I could probably do this while holding the shell, but I'll going to get rid of it. I don't want it to somehow get it the way.

1 vote for me to go straight to the final Bowser fight (nah, too soon), 1 vote for 7-1 (but this vote might've been intended for 4-1), 1 vote for me to replay a switch palace level and see if the switch respawned (I should do that at some point), 2 votes for me to become a creeper and explode (sssssss-BOOM!), 4 votes for me to perform silver muncher science (I'll get to that later), 2 votes for 5-2, 3 (maybe 4) votes for 4-1, and 4 votes for the ghost house! So, I'll visit the ghost house next!
This will give me quick access to a blue koopa, so that I can fly around the whole level.
I bet that P-switch is involved with the secret exit somehow...
I just noticed something: The "Yoshi drums" in the music didn't start up until I left Yoshi then landed back on him again. I wonder why the "Yoshi drums" weren't present from the start...
I'm going to Start+Select out and restart the level from midpoint.
And to the left, we have this shell. Now, the game's just giving me this shell, so it's probably important.
Oh, man. Bouncing off boos. If I'd tried normal jumping with the shell, I would've been screwed here!

Oh, so the SMB3 nipper plants are here too. They're usually not a big deal, except for that one in SMB3's 7-8 that spits tons of fireballs at you, and you should have picked up the hammer suit to defend yourself with there anyway.
Okay, that worked, somehow.
Alright, and now for the voting results...
Alright, so yeah. I'm going to go look for that secret exit.
Notice: If you don't happen to have a cape, you are exempt from the "must dive bomb after a bonus game perfect" law, so don't worry about that.
Oh, what's this? I don't think that spring was there before...
Found it! It was indeed offscreen, just above that upper ? block!
